tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE machine_learning_models (
   model_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
   model_name TEXT,
   model_type TEXT,
   trained_on TIMESTAMP,
   accuracy FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE model_metadata (
    model_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name TEXT,
    model_description TEXT,
    model_version INT,
    created_at TIMESTAMP,
    updated_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE model_configuration (
    config_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id UUID REFERENCES model_metadata(model_id),
    config_name TEXT,
    config_value JSONB,
    created_at TIMESTAMP,
    updated_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE MachineLearningModels (
    model_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    model_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    model_version INT NOT NULL,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE model_configuration (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(255),
    version INT,
    hyperparameters JSONB,
    created_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE model_metadata (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id UUID REFERENCES model_configuration(id),
    description TEXT,
    trained_on TIMESTAMP,
    accuracy FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE MachineLearningModel (
    model_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    hyperparameters JSONB,
    training_data_path VARCHAR(255),
    model_artifact BYTEA
);

CREATE TABLE ModelMetrics (
    metric_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT REFERENCES MachineLearningModel(model_id),
    accuracy FLOAT,
    precision FLOAT,
    recall FLOAT,
    f1_score FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE ModelRuns (
    run_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT REFERENCES MachineLearningModel(model_id),
    start_time TIMESTAMP,
    end_time TIMESTAMP,
    status VARCHAR(50)
);
